<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
Configuration
</h1>

<p>
StarryDrive can automatically animate visual parts and lets you tune the vehicle's handling through attributes.
</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
Visual Parts
</h2>

<p>
You can assign visual wheels and a steering wheel for StarryDrive to animate automatically.
</p>

<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
<li>Wheels rotate while driving.</li>
<li>The steering wheel rotates when steering.</li>
<li>Exhaust support is planned for a future update.</li>
</ul>

<p>
These parts are purely visual and do not affect the vehicle's physics.
</p>

<div class="rounded-xl border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/30 p-4">
<strong>Important:</strong> Only the <strong>PrimaryPart</strong> should have collisions enabled. Any additional parts, including decorative bumpers or wedges, should be <strong>Massless</strong> with collisions disabled.
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
Vehicle Attributes
</h2>

<table class="w-full border-collapse">
<thead>
<tr class="border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
<th class="text-left py-2">Attribute</th>
<th class="text-left py-2">Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>

<tr class="border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900">
<td class="py-3"><code>Acceleration</code></td>
<td>Controls how quickly the vehicle builds speed. Higher values provide stronger launches and allow the car to reach its top speed faster.</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900">
<td class="py-3"><code>MaxSpeed</code></td>
<td>The vehicle's maximum speed. As the car approaches this limit, acceleration is gradually reduced.</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900">
<td class="py-3"><code>TurnSpeed</code></td>
<td>Controls how quickly the vehicle changes its heading while steering.</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900">
<td class="py-3"><code>MaxSteer</code></td>
<td>Sets the maximum angle the visual front wheels can rotate.</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900">
<td class="py-3"><code>DriftStrength</code></td>
<td>
Higher values make steering feel more responsive and direct, especially while drifting. Lower values produce smoother, slower steering that takes longer to align with your steering input.
</td>
</tr>

<tr class="border-b border-zinc-100 dark:border-zinc-900">
<td class="py-3"><code>Suspension</code></td>
<td>
Controls suspension travel distance. Higher values create softer suspension, while lower values make the suspension stiffer. A value around <strong>3</strong> is a good starting point for most vehicles.
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td class="py-3"><code>TurnLift</code></td>
<td>
Tilts the vehicle during turns for a more dynamic appearance. While this can improve visuals, it can also interfere with the suspension raycasts. It's recommended to leave this at <strong>0</strong> while tuning your vehicle.
</td>
</tr>

</tbody>
</table>

<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">
Recommended Starting Values
</h2>

<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
<li><strong>TurnLift:</strong> <code>0</code></li>
<li><strong>Suspension:</strong> <code>3</code></li>
</ul>

<p>
Once the vehicle feels stable, you can fine-tune the remaining attributes to achieve the handling style you're aiming for.
</p>

</div>
